. ### Migration steps
The not flag on FilterFunction has been removed. So if you were using this in a data schema, store schema or view then you will need to wrap your function inside a Not filter function.
For example:
in json
json
"filter": {
  "functions": [
    {
      "function": {
        "class": "gaffer.function.simple.filter.Not",
        "function": {
          "class": "gaffer.function.simple.filter.IsEqual",
          "value": "user02"
        }
      },
      "selection": [
        {
          "key": "userId"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
in java using a view builder
java
.filter(new ElementFilter.Builder()
  .select(Property.USER_ID)
  .execute(new Not(new IsEqual("user02")))
  .build())
Any custom filter functions will also need to be migrated to implement the method
java
public boolean isValid(final Object[] input);
instead of 
java
protected boolean _isValid(final Object[] input);
There also are classes FilterFunctionTest, AggregateFunctionTest and TransformFunctionTest that should be extended when writing tests for any custom functions.
