. ## Migration Steps
The Graph and Store classes now have an additional 'User' parameter required for the execute methods.
The User object contains the id of the user executing the operation and any data authorisations the user has. The default constructor for User will create a user with ID = "UNKOWN".
REST API implementations that have user based requests should override the createUser method and return a User object, populated with the user's id and auths.
Previously the Accumulo store used an operation option for the user auths. Instead of adding that option, users should now create a User object with those auths. e.g:
Previously:
``` java
final GetRelatedEdges getRelatedEdges = new GetRelatedEdges.Builder()
    .addSeed(new EntitySeed("1"))
    .option(AccumuloStoreConstants.OPERATION_AUTHORISATIONS, "public,private")
    .build();
graph.execute(getRelatedEdges)
```
Now:
``` java
final User user01 = new User.Builder()
    .userId("user01")
    .dataAuth("public")
    .dataAuth("private")
    .build();
final GetRelatedEdges getRelatedEdges = new GetRelatedEdges.Builder()
    .addSeed(new EntitySeed("1"))
    .build();
graph.execute(getRelatedEdges, user01)
```
