The cache operations have been extended into a set of generic export operations. If you were previously using any of the cache operation then you will need to switch to using the relevant export operations instead.
For example, previously the cache operations were used as follows:
java
final OperationChain<Iterable<?>> cacheOpChain = new OperationChain.Builder()
  .first(new GetRelatedEdges.Builder<EntitySeed>()
          .addSeed(new EntitySeed("vertex1"))
          .build())
  .then(new UpdateCache())
  .then(new GenerateObjects.Builder<Edge, EntitySeed>()
          .generator(new EntitySeedExtractor())
          .build())
  .then(new GetRelatedEdges<EntitySeed>())
  .then(new UpdateCache())
  .then(new FetchCachedResult())
  .build();
This should now be written as:
java
final OperationChain<CloseableIterable<?>> exportOpChain = new OperationChain.Builder()
  .first(new InitialiseSetExport())
  .then(new GetRelatedEdges.Builder<EntitySeed>()
          .addSeed(new EntitySeed("vertex1"))
          .build())
  .then(new UpdateExport())
  .then(new GenerateObjects.Builder<Edge, EntitySeed>()
          .generator(new EntitySeedExtractor())
          .build())
  .then(new GetRelatedEdges<EntitySeed>())
  .then(new UpdateExport())
  .then(new FetchExport())
  .build();
