We have thought about creating a generator registry to avoid having to supply the CustomGenerator to the GenerateObjects operation and then Gaffer would automatically use the correct generator for you. However, selecting the correct generator to use isn’t always possible if there are multiple generators dealing with different domain objects - users would need to specify the type of domain object they wished to be returned.
As it stands, you could write an ElementGenerator implementation that could deal with all elements and correctly hand the elements off to the correct ElementGenerator automatically. This could be based on the element group (see gaffer.example.films.generator.DataGenerator, or a particular property value (such as 'domainClass').
. So we could check the table is configured in the same way Gaffer configures a table. When gaffer creates an Accumulo table it always removes the Accumulo Versioning iterator and adds a bloom filter property. It then adds a validator iterator and an aggregator iterator (if the schema has aggregators).
. It is surprisingly common for users to think they need to manually create a table in Accumulo before creating an AccumuloStore. If they do this then the table will not have the correct Bloom filters and iterators set, and this will cause poor performance and errors.
We should investigate setting a configuration property on a table when Gaffer creates it. Whenever a new store is created against that table, then the property could be checked, and if it is not present then the creation of the store should fail (if there are scenarios where experienced users may need to manually create a table and add iterators, then there could be an option on the store properties to ignore this warning, and carry on, but the default should be to fail).. ## Migration Steps
