If you have an existing table in accumulo or hbase and your schema does not have serialisers defined for all of your properties and vertices then you will need to add them in manually rather than relying on Gaffer to select them for you. This is because there have been changes to which serialisers it would automatically select for you.
The Serialisation Factories were updated to replace the deprecated raw serialisers with the new ordered serialisers. This will break the serialisation of all the serialised data that has been serialised with the Raw Serialisers and have not explicitly defined them in their schema. This would occur due to new serialisation factory selecting the new serialiser, which will not be compatible with the existing serialised bytes.. @james010101101 is this still required? Have you done any work on it?. Merged into develop.. Merged into develop.. Merged into develop.. Closing while I add some more tests.. # Migration steps
If you have any custom operations then you will need to make some minor changes.
Add the Required annotation to any required Operation fields.
Update your tests for your custom operations as follows:
OperationTest is now an abstract class, so for any custom Operation tests classes you will need to change:
java
public class CustomOperationTest implements OperationTest
java
public class CustomOperationTest extends OperationTest
Implement the new test method, getOperationClass(). For example:
java
@Override
public Class<? extends Operation> getOperationClass() {
    return CustomOperation.class;
}
If you have required fields then override the test method getRequiredFields() and return a Set containing the field names. For example:
java
@Override
protected Set<String> getRequiredFields() {
    return Sets.newHashSet("requiredField1", "requiredField2");
}
