Thanks for the suggestion. It is something we have thought about in the past and I agree it is something that would be useful. 
The issue is, for our Accumulo implementation, the pre and post filters are pushed down to Accumulo's iterators. At the moment the transform and post transform filter stages happen within the single REST server JVM. 
If we pushed the transform down to the iterators then the output from the transform would need to have an associated serialiser so it could be serialised back into bytes. Depending on what the user transformed, it could then break the Accumulo iterator. For example if a user wants to change the value of the source/destination or a groupBy property, then this would change the Key for the row in Accumulo and potentially cause the row to be out of order with the other rows.
We would need to introduce some sort of restricted transform that ensures serialisers are defined and ensures the transform only applies to non-groupBy properties. Or we need to work out a way of applying the transform in a way that doesn't break the accumulo iterators. If we do that then we could introduce your feature. And yes, that would be we would then be able to allow multiple sequences of filter-transform-filter-aggregate-filter.. Closing while changes are made.. Merged into develop.. Merged into develop.. Just one more minor comment. Then it'll be good to merge in. Thanks 👍 . Merged into develop.. # Migration Steps
