In version 1.8.1 the Join operation (first released in 1.8.0) was changed. The new operation outputs tuples keyed with 'LEFT' and 'RIGHT'. You can run a map operation over the output to extract a given side and run functions over it. Alternatively you could store either side in a set and run the Aggregate operation over it. This is why the operation was fundamentally changed in 1.8.1 to make it applicable to a wider variety of use cases
JoinFunctions which required iterating over both sides multiple times were removed for performance reasons. The remaining JoinFunctions are:
1) INNER - return only keys and values which matched
2) OUTER - return only keys which didn't match (along with their empty matches)
